title: Court tosses Trump lawsuit against Maryland judges over US deportations
summary: A federal judge nominated by Trump ruled that judges in Maryland have "absolute immunity" from lawsuits related to their judicial decisions. This ruling reinforces the legal principle that judges are protected from being sued for actions taken in their official capacity. The decision highlights ongoing discussions about judicial accountability and immunity in the legal system.
